observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the LCE require:
(a) the Municipal Budget Officer (MBO) to ensure that only expenditures which correspond to the identified gender issues and concerns in the GAD Plan are charged against the GAD Budget;
(b) the GAD Focal Person to carefully identify and include only PPAs that are gender responsive in the GAD Plan and Budget to address the issues and concerns arising from the unequal status of women and men stakeholders, clients and constituents of LGUs;
(c) establish and submit the details of accomplishment reports together with its supporting documents to validate the expenses charged to GAD fund.; and
(d) Municipal Planning and Development Officer (MPDO) to cause the setting up and maintenance of the GAD database which will serve as basis for planning, formulating GAD responsive projects, programs and activities.

We recommended that the LCE:
(a) require the MA to instruct the concerned personnel to maintain and update subsidiary records and prepare the schedules of all GSIS, PhilHealth and Pag-IBIG members of the Municipality on a monthly basis for proper monitoring of individual accounts;
(b) HRMO Officer to (i) make representations with the corresponding agencies to resolve the noted discrepancies; and (ii) keep the GSIS, PhilHealth and Pag-IBIG updated with the information of Municipal employees for their accurate billing.
